  "body": "when looking for a react root element the function would look at the 'container.firstChild' attribute, which is a convenience for childNodes[0]. this might be non-html nodes (#text for example), causing hierarchies containing spaces between the container and child (react root element) to fail locating the react root elem. modified to '.firstElementChild', which is a similar convenience for children[0]\n",
